terms.medium_def:
A woman living at the time of the Patriarchs, first mentioned at Gen.29.16; 
only referred to as Leah (לֵאָה); 
daughter of Laban; 
a sister of Rachel; 
wife of Israel; 
mother of Reuben, Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar, Zebulun and Dinah. § daughter of Laban, first wife of Jacob, and mother of Reuben, Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar, Zebulun, and Dinah

People from Aph(?) from the tribe of Judah, first mentioned at 1Ch.2.30; 
only referred to as Appaim (אַפַּיִם); 
descended from Nadab along with Seled; 
progenitors of Ishi. § a son of Nadab
